{
  "texts": [
    "We denote by K n, P n, and C n, respectively, the complete, path, and cycle graphs with n vertices.",
    "A vertex v ∈ V is simplicial in G when Adj(v) is a clique in G; v is universal when d v = n -1.The distance between two vertices u and v is the length of the shortest path between them, denoted by d(u, v).",
    "If there is no path between two vertices, d(u, v) = ∞.",
    "The vertex connectivity of a graph, denoted by κ(G), is the smallest number of vertices that, when removed, make the graph disconnected.",
    "A k-coloring of a graph G consists of assigning to each v ∈ V a color, from a set of k colors, in such a way that adjacent vertices receive different colors; the graph is then said to be k-colorable."
  ]
}